pageContext.claim: “You take Georgia. He was 10 points down when I endorsed him, he ended up winning by 40 points in the primary. He’s now in, but he was 10 points down. It was 70 to 30, something like that, 70-30 or 70-40, maybe 70-40. But it was an easy win.”
pageContext.analysis: Brian Kemp was not ten points down when Trump endorsed him; he was three points ahead. He did end up with a big victory in the primary.
